# UFO Matrix — Session Log: March 16, 2026

## Bugs Fixed

### HDR-001 — Case Boundary Merging in Bulk Ingest
**Problem:** `bulk_ingest.py` used a runtime regex (`NNN. CapitalLetter + Duration/Investigation`) to locate case headers in `bullard_vol2_raw.txt`. OCR damage garbled ~17 headers badly enough that the regex failed, causing consecutive cases to merge into a single oversized block. At a 33% failure rate in initial testing, bulk ingest could not proceed.

**Fix — `build_header_map.py`:**
A standalone pre-processing script that scans the raw text once and produces `header_map.json` — a precise JSON boundary map with one entry per case containing `line_start`, `line_end`, `encounter_id`, `retrieval_method`, and page stamps. `bulk_ingest.py` now consumes this map and slices text by line number instead of running a regex at runtime.

**Corrections applied (implemented exactly as specified by researcher against physical book):**

| Type | Count | Notes |
|------|-------|-------|
| False positive removals | 2 | Lines 6570 and 3174 — sentence fragments matching header regex |
| OCR remap (wrong case number) | 3 | Lines 1938→051, 5516→138, 8186→180a |
| OCR manual add (regex blind) | 14 | Cases with spaces, tildes, middle dots, letter/digit swaps |
| Master headers tagged | 9 | 187, 192–196, 198, 199, 201 — no motifs to extract |
| Manual/headerless cases | 20 | 181a, 195a–195q, 199_1/2/3 — emitted with null line positions |
| Duplicate case 058 | 1 hardcode | Two different cases both numbered 058 — disambiguated by line number |

**Output (`header_map.json`):**
```json
{
  "case_number": "136",
  "encounter_id": 137,
  "line_start": 4730,
  "line_end": 5490,
  "type": "case",
  "start_page_pdf": "100",
  "start_page_bullard": "C-80",
  "retrieval_method": "hypnosis"
}
```

